Kexim to Help Finance $4 Billion Kazakhstan Petrochemical Plant

-- B y   S u n g w o o   P a r k
-- 
2011-08-25T05:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/kexim-to-help-finance-4-billion-kazakhstan-petrochemical-plant.html
Export-Import Bank of  Korea  signed
an initial agreement with  Kazakhstan  Petrochemical Industries,
 LG Chem Ltd. (051910)  and Korea Trade Insurance Corp. to help finance a
$4 billion project to build a petrochemical plant in Kazakhstan,
the South Korean lender known as Kexim said in an e-mailed
statement today. The bank did not say how much funding it will
provide.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sungwoo Park in  Seoul  at 
 spark47@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
 Richard Dobson  at 
 rdobson4@bloomberg.net  